    "created_at": "2014-07-02T09:39:35Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-07-02T09:39:35Z",
    "body": "I'd really appreciate such a \"before-quit\" event, too. Here's what I'm trying to accomplish:\n\nWhen my app's main window is closed, it's not actually destroyed but simply hidden. This is necessary to keep the user connected in my app's integrated chat. When the dock icon is clicked, the hidden window is shown again.\n\nThe problem is now that I can't quit the app, since quit is only performed when all windows are gone. The \"before-quit\" event would allow me to handle the quit case properly, as I could destroy the window instead of just hiding it.\n\nLooking at the code for `Browser`, this should be pretty easy to achieve by emitting the event at the beginning of `Quit()`.\n"
  },
